<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="724" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="16.[195,1399,1826,2451]" pageId="16" pageNumber="724">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,545,2221,2254]" pageId="16" pageNumber="724">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Busuanga Squirrel is locally common and is successful in secondary forests and gardens. It is hunted at times because it can be an agricultural pest, butthis is unlikely to be a major threat. However, there is ongoing habitat loss due to conversion offorests to slash and burn areas that it does not tolerate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
